HEADWORD: Stomachical
<hw>Sto*mach"ic*al</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>stomachicus</ets>, Gr.
<?/: cf. F. <ets>stomachique</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or
pertaining to the stomach; <as>as, <ex>stomachic</ex>
vessels</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Strengthening to the stomach; exciting the action of
the stomach; stomachal; cordial.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stomachic</ent>⟦br⟧
